SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1109
By Haile
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Station Camp
High School wrestling team upon its success at
the Windsor Open.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly should pause to salute those
successful high school athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to
Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary group of young athletes is the Station Camp High
School wrestling team, whose members have proven themselves to be the fiercest of
competitors and truly worthy of admiration; and
WHEREAS, the Station Camp High School wrestling team represented Tennessee and
the U.S. at the Windsor Open, a freestyle wrestling tournament in Windsor, England, competing
against 400 athletes from forty countries; and
WHEREAS, the Bison were given the opportunity to compete internationally thanks to
freshman Memphis McCullough, who was invited to the Windsor Open by Team AAU Coach
Rob Pilcher; and
WHEREAS, under the astute leadership and inspiration of Head Coach Tyler Caron, the
members of the Station Camp wrestling team took home fifteen medals, proving themselves to
be formidable competitors with extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication; and
WHEREAS, in the Windsor Open tournament, Brodie Jaeckel and Eli Joles each won
gold in their respective weight classes, and Memphis McCullough earned a bronze medal; two-
time TSSAA champion Nate Graham finished second in the Seniors Division, while fellow state
placers Jay Hill, Lincoln Rich, and sophomore Derian Dotson also competed in the same
division. Lincoln Rich earned third place in his weight class, and Jay Hill competed in both the
U17 and Senior divisions, earning bronze medals in each; and
SJR1109
017565
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Head Coach Tyler Caron joined the tournament the night before it began
and finished runner-up in his first live competition in nearly two decades; and
WHEREAS, the Station Camp High School Bison epitomize all that is good in today's
student athletes, as they have achieved a premier level of success in competition while
exhibiting the highest degree of character in all aspects of life; and
WHEREAS, the perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent of this group of
young people not only made possible a successful season but also surely bode well for their
future success; and
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly find it appropriate to acknowledge
and applaud the Station Camp High School wrestling team on this special occasion; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the coaches and
athletes of the Station Camp High School wrestling team upon their success at the Windsor
Open tournament and extend to them our best wishes for every continued success in all their
future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
